{"word":"H8453 - תֹּושָׁב - tôwshâb - to-shawb' - Foreigner","slug":"H8453","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תֹּושָׁב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tôwshâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>to-shawb'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Foreigner"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D1;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D1; - to&#x0302;sha&#x0302;b  to&#x0302;sha&#x0302;b</b> - <i>to-shawb', to-shawb'</i><p/>(The second form used in Kings <a href='B:40 17:1'>Num 17:1</a>); from <a href=\"#/H3427\">H3427</a>; a <i>dweller</i> (but not outlandish, <a href=\"#/H5237\">H5237</a>); especially (as distinguished from a native citizen (active participle of <a href=\"#/H3427\">H3427</a>) and a temporary inmate, <a href=\"#/H1616\">H1616</a>, or mere lodger, <a href=\"#/H3885\">H3885</a>) resident <i>alien: - </i>foreigner-inhabitant, sojourner, stranger."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7617\">H7617</a>, <a href=\"#/H7618\">H7618</a>, <a href=\"#/H7619\">H7619</a>, <a href=\"#/H7622\">H7622</a>, <a href=\"#/H7628\">H7628</a>, <a href=\"#/H7629\">H7629</a>, <a href=\"#/H7630\">H7630</a>, <a href=\"#/H7633\">H7633</a>, <a href=\"#/H8664\">H8664</a>"}]}